<tp:treatment-sec sec-type="discussion">
<p>
Remarks.
For material examined and redescription, see 
<xref rid="ref329734">Ahrens (2004a)</xref>
. The distribution of this species is mainly in northern 
India
and the lower Himalaya (
<xref rid="ref329734">Ahrens 2004a</xref>
, 2006); in 
China
, it is known only from Ta-tsien-lu, the 
type
locality of 
<tp:taxon-name>Serica tsienluana Brenske, 1897</tp:taxon-name>
. No recent records are known.
</p>
